                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d557">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60H31/148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Yugoslavia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-17T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 17, 1938—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>48. Your 164, November 15, 6 p.m. (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) We have no objection
                    to a unilateral declaration as you propose, (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) Such a
                    declaration might be given in the form of a memorandum. However, (<hi
                        rend="italic">c</hi>) there should be no acknowledging note.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
